sin límites -- tRonda nocturna: A Homage to Buenos Aires -- tContributors -- tIndex of Terms -- tIndex of Names -- tIndex of Concepts0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  a2016 CHOICE Outstanding Academic TitleDespite All Adversities examines a representative selection of notable queer films by Spanish America's most important directors since the 1950s. Each chapter focuses on a single film and offers rich and thoughtful new interpretations by a prominent scholar. The book explores films from across the region, including Tomás Gutiérrez Alea's and Juan Carlos Tabío's Fresa y chocolate (Strawberry and Chocolate, 1993), Marcelo Piñeyro's Plata quemada (Burnt Money, 2000), Barbet Schroeder's La Virgen de los Sicarios (Our Lady of the Assassins, 2000), Lucía Puenzo's XXY (XXY, 2007), Francisco J. Lombardi's No se lo digas a nadie (Don't Tell Anyone, 1998), Arturo Ripstein's El lugar sin límites (Hell Without Limits, 1978), among others. A survey of recent lesbian-themed Mexican films is also included.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aGay people in motion pictures. 0aGays in motion pictures. 0aHispanic Americans in the motion picture industry. 0aHomosexuality in motion pictures. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Lesbian / Gay Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh1 aBalderston, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastillo, Debra A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastillo, Debra A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCastro Ricalde, María de la 